Bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil for the potatoes.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer). Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{4} (or use a #garlic press{}).

When boiling, add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%mins}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%grams} to the pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the chicken is cooked, add a drizzle of oil if the pan is dry.

Sprinkle over the @plain flour{1%tbsp}, then add the garlic and @curry powder mix{1%sachet}. Stir together and cook for ~{1%min}.

Pour in the @water{100%ml} for the sauce and stir in the @chicken stock paste{10%grams}. Bring to the boil and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%mins}.

Stir the @creme fraiche{150%grams}, @mango chutney{40%grams} and @peas{120%grams} through the sauce. Bring to the boil and remove from the heat.

Taste the sauce and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat. Add a @butter{knob} and a splash of @?milk{1%splash} and mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with salt and pepper.

Preheat your #grill{} to high.

Transfer the chicken mixture to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}, then spoon over the creamy mash, using the back of a #spoon{} to smooth it out.

Use a #fork{} to make lines all the way up and down the mash.

Drizzle with a little @oil{}, then grill on the top shelf of your oven until golden brown, ~{8-9%mins}.

When ready, serve between your bowls. Enjoy!